            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><h3>Open house - "Beyond Billings: Stories and Belonging(s)"</h3>
<p>Wednesday, April 23 from 10 am to 8 pm<br>
Free admission</p>
<p>Celebrate the opening of our latest exhibition: "Beyond Billings: Stories and Belonging(s)" with free admission to Billings Estate National Historic Site and extended operating hours on Wednesday, April 23. Drop by between 10 am and 8 pm to explore Ottawa’s oldest wood-framed house and to learn more about a unique selection of artefacts from the Billings Estate collection.</p>
<p><strong>About the exhibition: "</strong>Beyond Billings: Stories and Belonging(s)" showcases a selection of artefacts from the Billings Estate National Historic Site collection chosen by twelve individual curators. "Beyond Billings" explores how museum objects are perceived from different viewpoints. Each object in this exhibition is highlighted in a vignette – a brief but powerful glimpse of moments in time – inviting visitors to consider the object’s life beyond its arrival to the Billings family. "Beyond Billings" is a collaboration between Carleton University’s Curatorial Studies Program and the City of Ottawa Museums and Historic Sites.</p>
<p>*Please note that the "Beyond Billings" exhibition is located on the second floor of the museum and is only accessible by stairs. A visual aid will be available for those unable to access the exhibition. The primary exhibition, “The Billings Family Story”, can be explored on the ground floor. If you have questions or concerns regarding accessibility, please contact the museum at 613-580-2088 or by email at <a href="mailto:museums@ottawa.ca">museums@ottawa.ca</a>. Additional <a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/node/1007407">information about accessibility</a> can be found on the museum webpage.</p>
